\frac{\partial f}{\partial y}(\alpha(p))\neq 0
z=g(x,y)
p=(x_0,y_0,z_0)
F(x,y,g(x,y))=0
\frac{\partial g}{\partial x}=-\frac{\frac{\partial F}{\partial x}}{\frac{\partial F}{\partial z}}=\frac{y}{x}\cdot\frac{\frac{\partial f}{\partial x}}{\frac{\partial f}{\partial y}}+\frac{z}{x}
\frac{\partial g}{\partial y}=-\frac{\frac{\partial F}{\partial y}}{\frac{\partial F}{\partial z}}=-\frac{\frac{\partial f}{\partial x}}{\frac{\partial f}{\partial y}}
x\cdot\frac{\partial g}{\partial x}+y\cdot\frac{\partial g}{\partial y}=x\cdot\Bigg( \frac{y}{x}\cdot\frac{\frac{\partial f}{\partial x}}{\frac{\partial f}{\partial y}}+\frac{z}{x}\Bigg)-y\cdot\frac{\frac{\partial f}{\partial x}}{\frac{\partial f}{\partial y}}=z=g(x,y)
